name: Appendix E: Summary of Information - Pass once confirmed
Routine inspection checklist for Body-Protected electrical areas
This checklist shall beused in accordance with Clause 8.2.7
Note: The checklist may be in a different format and may be recorded electronically
8.2.1.1: Inspection - All electrical equipment and fittings in good condition
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Circuit identification visible and intact on each
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Protected points labelled as to which RCD protects them
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Circuit identification visible and intact on each LIM
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Overload monitors labelled with alarm setting
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Socket-outlets protected by RCD labelled 'RCD PROTECTED'
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Socket-outlets protected by isolating transformers labelled 'ISOLATING TRANSFORMER PROTECTED'
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Socket-outlets intended for cleaning purposes labelled 'CLEANING PURPOES ONLY'
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Body-protected electrical area sign - Still Visible
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Body-protected electrical area sign - Labelled with current inspection date
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Body-protected electrical area sign - Labelled with identity of authorised person
8.2.1.2: Labelling - Body-protected electrical area sign - Labelled with next test date
8.2.1.3.1: Socket-outlets coloured according to type of supply
8.2.1.3.2: If RCD protected, power-available indicator operational
8.2.1.3.2: Number of socket-outlets and permanently wired electrical equipment protected by RCD does not exceed 12
8.2.1.3.2: On/Off luminous indicators operational, if applicable
8.2.1.3.2: Socket-outlets double-poled if protected by a transformer-isolated supply
8.2.1.3.2: All socket-outlets below 2.3m protected by LPD
8.2.1.3.2: Confirm that when a fault is applied to each socket-outlet within patient area or within 2.0m of entrance of the patient area, the RCD trips
8.2.1.3.2: Confirm that when a fault is applied to each socket-outlet within patient area or within 2.0m of entrance of the patient area causes a response on LIM
Confirm that the earth pins of all socket-outlets below 2.3m are earthed to less than 1.0-Ohm
Confirm that the earth pins of all socket-outlets within 2.0m of entrance to patient area are earthed to less than 1.0-Ohm
Confirm that all socket-outlets used by medical electrical equipment accessible above 2.3m are earthed to less than 1.0-Ohm
Confirm that all permanently wired electrical equipment with conductive parts below 2.3m are earthed to less than 1.0-Ohm
8.2.3.2: RCD Sensitivity for Australia - Confirm that the RCD trips between 4.5-10.5 mA
8.2.3.3: RCD Tripping times for Australia - Confirm this by carrying out at least two such tests
8.2.3.5: RCD Supply available indicator lights - If applicable, confirm that they are operational
8.2.3.6: Audiovisual RCD Trip Indicators - If applicable, confirm that they are operational
Confirm that the hazard current is below 2.00mA
For routine testing, the PHC under normal conditions of operation shall be verified by applying the following process to each transformer Line Isolation Overload Monitor (LIOM)
All electrical equipment are disconnected from the supply
The current flowing through a low impedance ammeter connected between one isolated supply conductor and earth is noted
The test is repeated for the other isolated supply conductor. The larger of the noted values is the prospective hazard current. It shall be less than 2mA
The prospective hazard current of the supply is recorded in the commissioning checklist
Confirm that a load of 110-120% of transformer rated current causes the alarm to activate in 3-5 Seconds
Confirm that UPS status indicator performance is routinely verified
Checks completed to specification/drawings - Area left clean & tidy
FINAL - Pass when happy to proceed with work(s) (Any issues please comment below)

name: Is the communications riser ready for communications rack installation
Riser must be in a finished dust-free state, finished floors, cable tray installed, clean and permanent doors installed
Does the communications rack match the approved technical data
Has the communications rack been installed in position as per the Appselec communications riser elevation shop drawings and floor plan layout
Has the communications rack been fixed to the floor using appropriate fixings
Are the doors and side panels installed and free from damage
Does the communications rack comply with all the relevant clearances
Are door swings and access to the communications rack unobstructed
Has the communications rack been permanently labelled with a traffolyte label or similar on the door
Check that the label matches the communications rack layouts
Has the Appselec label/logo been fixed to the front of the communications rack
Has a CET been installed adjacent to/or within the communications rack and has a 6 mm2 green/yellow earth cable been terminated to the CET
Refer to Communications SLD for earth cabling schematic
Has an earth bar been installed adjacent to/or within the communications rack and has a 6 mm2 green/yellow earth been terminated to the earth bar from the CET
Has the 6 mm2 green/yellow earth been identified and labelled with “Communications Earth” at the originating electrical distribution board
Does the FOBOT match the approved technical data
Has the FOBOT been installed in the correct rack RU position as per the communications rack layout
Has the FOBOT been labelled permanently with traffolyte label or similar
Has a service loop been provided in the optical fibre cable
Has the fibre port arrangement on the FOBOT been detailed and labelled
Do the fibre adapters on the FOBOT match the type of fibre being used
Adapters, pigtail connector colours must match, fibre cable type must match
Have fibre protective caps been installed on all fibre adapter ports
Does the Cat 6/6A patch panels match the approved technical data
Have the Cat 6/6A patch panels been installed in correct rack RU position as per the communications rack layout
Have the Cat 6/6A patch panel ports been labelled permanently with traffolyte label or similar
Have cable wrap-around labels been attached to each individual Cat 6/6A cable behind the patch panels
Have the Cat 6/6A patch panels been earthed with 2.5 mm2 green/yellow earth cable from the earth bar within the communications rack? (Shielded patch panels only)
Have horizontal cable managers been installed in the correct rack RU position as per the communications rack layout
Have vertical cable managers been installed in the correct rack RU position as per the communications rack layout
Has the correct power been provided for the communications racks
Check for captive outlets? Are there 2x or 1x? Are they 10A, 15A or 20A? Check the Appselec power floor layouts against the communications specification
Do the PDU’s match the approved technical data
Have the PDU’s been installed in position as per the communications rack layout
Have the PDU’s been plugged into the captive outlets/rack mounted UPS as detailed on the communications rack layouts
Have the PDU’s been labelled appropriately detailing the power source
For example UPS supply (Generator backed) DB-XX
Is the communications rack/riser ready for UPS installation
Riser must be in a finished dust-free state, finished floors, cable tray installed, clean and permanent doors installed
Does the UPS match the approved technical data
Has the UPS been installed in position as per the communications rack layouts
Has the UPS been labelled appropriately detailing the power source
For example UPS supply (Generator backed) DB-XX
Has any associated Battery Backup for the UPS been installed as per the communications rack layouts and is it connected
Has the UPS been commissioned? Refer to UPS ITP for commissioning details
Is the communications rack/riser ready for Active Equipment installation
Riser must be in a finished dust-free state, finished floors, cable tray installed, clean and permanent doors installed
Does the Active Equipment need to be configured prior to installation within the communications rack
Does the Active Equipment match the approved technical data
Has the Active Equipment been installed in the correct rack RU position as per the communications rack layouts
Do you have a network diagram detailing the connection and labelling of all Active Equipment
Has the Active Equipment been labelled appropriately as per the vendor requirements
All switches are to be labelled with the correct vendor labelling convention
Have SFPs been provided and installed
Check that they are the correct SFP for the optical fibre cable installed
Check they are installed into the correct port
(SFP is a small form-factor pluggable transceiver)
Have stacker cables been provided to stack switches together
Are they connected as per the integrator/vendor requirements
Have the switches been connected to the PDUs
Check if switches require one supply or two supplies (dual power redundancy)
Check if switches require UPS supply/UPS + generator supply
Do you have the correct length, colour, type (Cat6/6A) and quantity of patch leads
Do you have a patching schedule detailing which switch port patches to which patch panel port
Do you have the appropriate cable management capacity installed to patch cables as per the patching schedule
